This paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper uses mobile phone data to estimate food consumption and poverty indices, which involves analyzing social networks and information flows. 

2. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper addresses issues related to economic development and humanitarian action, which are relevant to the intersection of computers and society. 

3. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses computational methods to analyze mobile phone data and estimate food security indicators. 

4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may involve issues related to data privacy and security, as it deals with sensitive information such as call detail records and airtime credit purchases. 

5. cs.SD (Software Development and Programming) - The paper may involve the development of software tools or algorithms to analyze mobile phone data and estimate food security indicators.
